<item rdf:about="http://idle.slashdot.org/story/11/10/03/1542214/Judge-Rules-Bosss-Firing-Contest-Created-a-Hostile-Work-Environment?utm_source=rss1.0mainlinkanon&amp;utm_medium=feed">
<title>Judge Rules Boss's "Firing Contest" Created a Hostile Work Environment</title>
<link>http://idle.slashdot.org/story/11/10/03/1542214/Judge-Rules-Bosss-Firing-Contest-Created-a-Hostile-Work-Environment?utm_source=rss1.0mainlinkanon&amp;utm_medium=feed</link>
<description>Branded the "boss from hell" by his employees, 57-year-old William Ernst lost a court battle with ex-workers over unemployment benefits. An Iowa judge has decided that Ernst's "firing contest" memo wasn't the best management strategy, saying, "The employer&amp;rsquo;s actions have clearly created a hostile work environment by suggesting its employees turn on each other for a minimal monetary prize. This was an intolerable and detrimental work environment.&amp;rdquo; The memo reads in part: "New Contest &amp;ndash; Guess The Next Cashier Who Will Be Fired!!! To win our game, write on a piece of paper the name of the next cashier you believe will be fired. Write their name [the person who will be fired], today's date, today's time, and your name. Seal it in an envelope and give it to the manager to put in my envelope."&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fidle.slashdot.org%2Fstory%2F11%2F10%2F03%2F1542214%2Fjudge-rules-bosss-firing-contest-created-a-hostile-work-environment%3Futm_source%3Dslashdot%26utm_medium%3Dfacebook" target="_blank" title="Share on Facebook"&gt;&lt;img src="http://a.fsdn.com/sd/facebook_icon_large.png"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
   
      &lt;a href="http://twitter.com/home?status=Judge+Rules+Boss's+%22Firing+Contest%22+Created+a+Hostile+Work+Environment%3A+http%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2FqEvi0E" target="_blank" title="Share on Twitter"&gt;&lt;img src="http://a.fsdn.com/sd/twitter_icon_large.png"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://idle.slashdot.org/story/11/10/03/1542214/Judge-Rules-Bosss-Firing-Contest-Created-a-Hostile-Work-Environment?utm_source=rss1.0moreanon&amp;amp;utm_medium=feed"&gt;Read more of this story&lt;/a&gt; at Slashdot.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
<dc:creator>samzenpus</dc:creator>
